\pard\f0\fs28    Sect. PSAMMOSERIS (Boiss. & Reuter) Babcock. More or less pubescent annuals or perennials. Basal leaves petiolate, dentate to pinnate. Capitula with few to many florets. Ligules yellow, reddish or dirty green on outer face. Receptacle with ciliate pits.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 69. C. bellidifolia} Loisel.,{\i  Fl. Gall.} 527 (1807). Annual; stems 35-50 cm, remotely branched from near the base. Leaves glabrous or pubescent on midrib beneath: basal up to 11 × 3 cm, oblanceolate, entire to pinnately lobed, narrowed at base; cauline like the basal or sessile, auriculate-amplexicaul. Ligules reddish on outer face. Involucre 7-10 × 4-5 mm; bracts linear-lanceolate, obtuse, glabrous, tomentulose or glandular-pubescent, the outer 1/4-1/3 as long as inner. Achenes 3·5-6·5 mm, yellowish or brownish, fusiform, attenuate into a slender beak, 10-ribbed. 2n = 8. •{\i  W. Mediterranean region.} ?Bl Co Ga Hs It Sa.
\par 

