\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. H. hispanica} Barnades ex Lam.,{\i  Encycl. Méth. Bot.}{\b  3}: 134 (1789). Indumentum of both short, stellate hairs, and long, patent, simple hairs up to 12 mm. Stems 2-30 cm, one to several. Basal and cauline leaves similar, 10-60 × 2-10 mm, linear, linear-oblanceolate or spathulate, obtuse, entire. Peduncles thickened at apex after anthesis. Involucre 8-12 × 8-12 mm; bracts linear to linear-lanceolate, more or less acute, strongly incurved and thickened in fruit. Achenes c. 1·3 mm. 2n = 18.{\i  Sandy fields and dry waste places. • C. Spain, N. Portugal, mainly in the mountains.} Hs Lu.
